flowRoot.flowPara: The main perspective for loading, selecting and plotting data.
Image plot action buttons additionally include (l-r):
Rescale image colourmap for data in view
This view shows the available dataset in the selected file, and their shape.
Check the box to activate the dataset for display.
This drop-down can be used to change how the data is displayed (Line, Image...).
The table is used to slice images from a stack or view subsections of multi-dimensional data.
It also allows axes to be assigned to each dimension.
Toggle autoscale when new data plotted
Main plot window, clicking on the Plot tab maximises this view.
Additional options on right click menu.
Loaded files are displayed here. Check the box to activate the file for display.
Files can be loaded by drag-drop here.
Quick load widget can be used to quickly load another file from the current directory
More features (viewing Nexus Tree, filtering datasets, changing line trace colors) can be found in the top level menu items
